She said in a low voice, that it was very late.  To-morrow.

âNow I see what you want,â said Tugby; âand what you mean.  You know
there are two parties in this house about you, and you delight in setting
âem by the ears.  I donât want any quarrels; Iâm speaking softly to avoid
a quarrel; but if you donât go away, Iâll speak out loud, and you shall
cause words high enough to please you.  But you shanât come in.  That I
