and always making disturbances between man and wife, youâd be better out
of it.  Go along with you.â

âFollow her!  To desperation!â

Again the old man heard the voices.  Looking up, he saw the figures
hovering in the air, and pointing where she went, down the dark street.

âShe loves it!â he exclaimed, in agonised entreaty for her.  âChimes! she
loves it still!â

âFollow her!â  The shadow swept upon the track she had taken, like a
